(11, 4, '27 Natural Health and Nutrition Tips That Are Evidence-Based', 'blog-details/27-natural-health-and-nutrition-tips-that-are-evidence-based', 'If you want to boost your health and wellbeing, there are plenty of natural and home remedies to choose from, ranging from avoiding charred meats and added sugars to practicing meditation.', '<div class=\"css-1i3umih\" style=\"-webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; box-sizing: inherit;\"><div style=\"-webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; box-sizing: inherit;\"><p class=\"css-w2pt6r\" style=\"-webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; box-sizing: inherit; margin-bottom: 30px; line-height: 36px;\">If you want to boost your health and wellbeing, there are plenty of natural and home remedies to choose from, ranging from avoiding charred meats and added sugars to practicing meditation.</p></div><p style=\"-webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; box-sizing: inherit; margin-bottom: 25px; line-height: 26px;\">When it comes to knowing what’s healthy, even qualified experts often seem to hold opposing opinions. This can make it difficult to figure out what you should actually be doing to optimize your health.</p><div data-preamp=\"serena-chatbot\" style=\"-webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; box-sizing: inherit;\"></div><p style=\"-webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; box-sizing: inherit; margin-bottom: 25px; margin-top: 25px; line-height: 26px;\">Yet, despite all the disagreements, a number of wellness tips are well supported by research.</p><p style=\"-webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; box-sizing: inherit; margin-bottom: 25px; margin-top: 25px; line-height: 26px;\">Here are 27 health and nutrition tips that are based on scientific evidence.</p><div style=\"-webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; box-sizing: inherit;\"><figure class=\"css-yhe8zq\" style=\"-webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; box-sizing: inherit; margin: 30px auto; max-width: 1296px;\"><span class=\"css-rwmw5v\" style=\"-webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; box-sizing: inherit; display: block; text-align: center; line-height: 0; outline: none; position: relative; user-select: none; z-index: 0;\"><span class=\"css-mjp0j9\" style=\"-webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; box-sizing: inherit; display: block; position: relative; padding-bottom: 421.288px;\"><picture class=\"css-16pk1is\" style=\"-webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; box-sizing: inherit; line-height: 0;\"><source srcset=\"//i0.wp.com/post.healthline.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/track-running-water-exercise-drinking-1296x728-header.jpg?w=1575 750w\" media=\"(min-width: 1190px)\" style=\"-webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; box-sizing: inherit;\"><source srcset=\"//i0.wp.com/post.healthline.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/track-running-water-exercise-drinking-1296x728-header.jpg?w=1575 750w\" media=\"(min-width: 990px)\" style=\"-webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; box-sizing: inherit;\"><source srcset=\"//i0.wp.com/post.healthline.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/track-running-water-exercise-drinking-1296x728-header.jpg?w=1845 879w\" media=\"(min-width: 768px)\" style=\"-webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; box-sizing: inherit;\"><img src=\"https://i0.wp.com/post.healthline.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/track-running-water-exercise-drinking-1296x728-header.jpg?w=1155&amp;h=1528\" alt=\"\" class=\"css-1jytyml\" style=\"-webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; box-sizing: inherit; user-select: none; max-width: 100%; left: 0px; bottom: 0px; position: absolute;\"></picture></span><hl-share-overlay class=\"css-18moxll\" style=\"-webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; box-sizing: inherit; display: flex; align-items: flex-start; justify-content: flex-start; position: absolute; inset: 0px; z-index: 1; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; opacity: 0; padding: 20px;\"><a class=\"icon-hl-pinterest css-16c90h6\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopene